    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "To add further detail here. See this section of the spec: https://github.com/ethereum/devp2p/blob/master/discv5/discv5-wire.md#udp-communication\r\n\r\nBecause an ENR can be at most 300 bytes and the max packet size is 1280 bytes, we can fit at most 4 ENR's per Nodes response. Any request should return at most 16 peers, so accounting for extra encoding bytes etc a Nodes response shouldn't have or need a total > 5. \r\n\r\nI guess in principle you could follow the spec and just send a single ENR per Nodes response, but this would be fairly inefficient and they should probably be grouped.",
